{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DCUWZ1DtbXeq6Dw9EEqkBm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Cloche Workflow DSL Exploration Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's a comprehensive overview of the workflow DSL parsing, step definitions, domain types, and agent configuration:\n\n### 1. **Lexer and Parser Structure**\n\n**Lexer** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`):\n- Tokenizes workflow DSL input into basic tokens: identifiers, strings, integers, brackets, braces, operators\n- Supports single-line comments (`//`)\n- Handles quoted strings with escape sequences (`\\\"`, `\\\\`, `\\n`, `\\t`)\n- Supports hyphenated identifiers like `simple-build`\n\n**Parser** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`):\n- Two-token lookahead parser\n- Entry points:\n  - `Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption)` - Single workflow with optional location\n  - `ParseForContainer(input string)` - Container workflow\n  - `ParseForHost(input string)` - Host workflow\n  - `ParseAll(input string)` - Multiple workflows (defaults to container)\n  - `ParseAllForHost(input string)` - Multiple host workflows\n\n**Token Types** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go`):\n```go\nTokenEOF, TokenIllegal, TokenIdent, TokenInt, TokenString,\nTokenLBrace, TokenRBrace, TokenLBracket, TokenRBracket,\nTokenLParen, TokenRParen, TokenComma, TokenEquals,\nTokenArrow, TokenColon, TokenDot\n```\n\n### 2. **Domain Types**\n\n**Step** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 35-40):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string              // unique step identifier\n    Type    StepType            // agent, script, or workflow\n    Results []string            // possible outcomes (e.g., [success, fail])\n    Config  map[string]string   // step configuration\n}\n```\n\n**Step Type** (lines 14-20):\n```go\ntype StepType string\n\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    StepType = \"agent\"    // has 'prompt' field\n    StepTypeScript   StepType = \"script\"   // has 'run' field\n    StepTypeWorkflow StepType = \"workflow\" // has 'workflow_name' field (host only)\n)\n```\n\n**Workflow** (lines 135-143):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation        // \"host\" or \"container\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire                  // result → next step mappings\n    Collects  []Collect               // multi-condition wiring\n    EntryStep string                  // first step to execute\n    Config    map[string]string       // workflow-level config\n}\n```\n\n**Wire** (lines 42-47):\n```go\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string                  // source step name\n    Result    string                  // result name\n    To        string                  // target step name\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping          // env var injections\n}\n```\n\n**OutputPath** (lines 62-64):\n```go\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment\n}\n```\n\nSupports navigation like: `output.key`, `output[0]`, `output.a.b.c`, `output.items[0].name`\n\n**WorkflowLocation** (lines 22-33):\n```go\nconst (\n    LocationContainer WorkflowLocation = \"container\"  // runs in Docker container\n    LocationHost      WorkflowLocation = \"host\"       // runs on host machine\n)\n```\n\n### 3. **Workflow DSL Syntax**\n\n**Basic Structure** (`docs/workflows.md`, lines 85-117):\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"3\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail    -> abort\n  test:success      -> done\n  test:fail         -> fix\n  fix:success       -> test\n  fix:fail          -> abort\n  fix:give-up       -> abort\n}\n```\n\n**Step Type Inference** (parser.go, lines 268-297):\n- Inferred from content: exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name` required\n- Agent step: has `prompt` field\n- Script step: has `run` field\n- Workflow step: has `workflow_name` field (host workflows only)\n\n**Workflow Configuration Blocks**:\n- `container { }` - Sets image, agent_command, agent_args, network_allow\n- `host { }` - Marks as host workflow, sets agent_command, agent_args\n\n### 4. **Agent Configuration**\n\n**Prompt Adapter** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`, lines 19-53):\n\n```go\ntype Adapter struct {\n    Commands           []string          // ordered fallback chain (e.g., [\"claude\", \"gemini\"])\n    ExplicitArgs       []string          // overrides default args if non-nil\n    RunID              string\n    StatusWriter       *protocol.StatusWriter\n    ResumeConversation bool              // for conversation resume mode\n}\n\nvar defaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n}\n```\n\n**Agent Configuration Hierarchy** (resolution order):\n1. Step-level: `agent_command` and `agent_args` in step config\n2. Workflow-level: `container.agent_command` and `container.agent_args` (container workflows) or `host.agent_command` and `host.agent_args` (host workflows)\n3. Environment variable: `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`\n4. Default: `\"claude\"`\n\n**Container Workflow Agent Resolution** (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`, lines 55-63):\n```go\nif cmd, ok := os.LookupEnv(\"CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND\"); ok {\n    promptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n}\nif cmd := wf.Config[\"container.agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n    promptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n}\nif args := wf.Config[\"container.agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n    promptAdapter.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n}\n```\n\n**Host Workflow Agent Resolution** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`, lines 225-242):\n```go\nadapter := prompt.New()\n\n// Apply workflow-level agent config\nif len(e.AgentCommands) > 0 {\n    adapter.Commands = e.AgentCommands\n}\nif len(e.AgentArgs) > 0 {\n    adapter.ExplicitArgs = e.AgentArgs\n}\n\n// Step-level overrides\nif cmd := step.Config[\"agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n    adapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n}\nif args := step.Config[\"agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n    adapter.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n}\n```\n\n**ParseCommands Function** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`, lines 55-67):\nSplits comma-separated agent_command string: `\"claude,gemini\"` → `[\"claude\", \"gemini\"]`\n\n### 5. **Known Step Config Keys**\n\n(`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 246-257):\n```go\nvar knownStepConfigKeys = map[string]bool{\n    \"prompt\":        true,\n    \"run\":           true,\n    \"max_attempts\":  true,\n    \"timeout\":       true,\n    \"agent_command\": true,     // step-level override\n    \"agent_args\":    true,     // step-level override\n    \"results\":       true,\n    \"feedback\":      true,     // include previous step feedback\n    \"workflow_name\": true,\n    \"prompt_step\":   true,     // override source for prompt content\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Test Files**\n\n**DSL Parser Tests** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`):\n- Full workflow parsing\n- Minimal workflows\n- Container blocks at workflow and step level\n- Host block location detection\n- Output path expressions\n- Collect conditions (all/any)\n- Conflict detection between host/container blocks\n\n**Prompt Adapter Tests** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`):\n- Command execution with feedback\n- Max attempts limiting\n- Fallback chain handling (command not found, non-zero exit without marker)\n- Result marker detection (CLOCHE_RESULT:success/fail)\n- Output file writing\n- Attempt count tracking\n- `ParseCommands()` function tests\n\n**Domain Validation Tests** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow_test.go`):\n- Step type inference\n- Wiring validation\n- Unreachable step detection\n- Duplicate result mapping detection\n- Output path evaluation\n\n### 7. **File Locations**\n\n**Core DSL:**\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` - Lexical analysis\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go` - Token definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Parser implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain types and validation\n\n**Agent Adapters:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` - Prompt agent implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` - Script/run adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` - AgentAdapter interface\n\n**Execution:**\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - Container workflow execution\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host workflow execution\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/` - Workflow graph traversal engine\n\n**Documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Complete DSL syntax and semantics\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` - Project overview and architecture\n\n### 8. **Key Type Definitions Summary**\n\n| Type | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| `Step` | domain/workflow.go:35 | Single workflow step definition |\n| `Workflow` | domain/workflow.go:135 | Complete workflow graph |\n| `Wire` | domain/workflow.go:42 | Step→step result routing |\n| `OutputPath` | domain/workflow.go:62 | JSON path expressions |\n| `Adapter` (prompt) | adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go:25 | Agent execution wrapper |\n| `Parser` | dsl/parser.go:11 | DSL parser state machine |\n| `Lexer` | dsl/lexer.go:3 | Token stream generator |\n| `StepType` | domain/workflow.go:14 | Enum: agent/script/workflow |\n| `WorkflowLocation` | domain/workflow.go:23 | Enum: container/host |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a01a5fba7e4fd81b4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60715\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 47509</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4704652e-bf3d-4290-bbe9-3b856a038a11","uuid":"0230655d-523a-4dab-838e-5200532a4bb9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the Cloche codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The workflow DSL parsing - find the lexer, parser, AST types\n2. How steps (especially prompt steps) are defined in the DSL and parsed\n3. The domain types for Workflow, Step, etc.\n4. How agent configuration currently works in prompt steps\n5. Any existing test files for the DSL parser\n\nLook in internal/domain/, any parser/lexer directories, and docs/workflows.md for the DSL syntax. Give me file paths, key type definitions, and relevant code snippets.","agentId":"a01a5fba7e4fd81b4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Cloche Workflow DSL Exploration Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's a comprehensive overview of the workflow DSL parsing, step definitions, domain types, and agent configuration:\n\n### 1. **Lexer and Parser Structure**\n\n**Lexer** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`):\n- Tokenizes workflow DSL input into basic tokens: identifiers, strings, integers, brackets, braces, operators\n- Supports single-line comments (`//`)\n- Handles quoted strings with escape sequences (`\\\"`, `\\\\`, `\\n`, `\\t`)\n- Supports hyphenated identifiers like `simple-build`\n\n**Parser** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`):\n- Two-token lookahead parser\n- Entry points:\n  - `Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption)` - Single workflow with optional location\n  - `ParseForContainer(input string)` - Container workflow\n  - `ParseForHost(input string)` - Host workflow\n  - `ParseAll(input string)` - Multiple wor